This paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a method for boosting the performance of unsupervised techniques, which involves the injection of implicit pairs into unpaired sets. This method involves learning a mapping between two domains, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the compatibility of distributions, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
